Ethics has been applied to analyze human use of Earth's limited resources. The material limits of [[Earth]], its [[carrying capacity]] in particular, affects what people decide is right and wrong. This has led to the study of [[environmental ethics]], [[social ecology]], and the [[green movement]]. [[Deep ecology]] is a philosophy which holds that humans must do what is good for the Earth's biosphere, and not what is good for humans. Only by doing so can people survive.
